@NODE WhatIsIt "WhatIsIt"

    Welcome to MakethemYS, the Doors Util Made for MebbsNet Pro.
    With This Door, you can View Any file which exists on the BBS
    online.Most of the archiviers used in the Amiga world are known to
    Makethemys.
    You Can also extract Any File from ANY Archive on the bbs sothat
    you can put it in your own Archive which can be downloaded
    after you made your chose which files you want to put in your self
    created archive.
    You can also choose to create a Non Compressed archive, this way,
    you can select a textfile in a archive which can be downloaded real
    fast.
    Even DMS Files are FULLY supported in this door, if you select a DMS
    file, and you want to extract a file from it, you HAVE to enter
    not only the filename but also the directory name in which the file
    you choose resides.

    You Can view Text/ASCII files On-line Before you decide to download
    the whole archive, You can even View Files which are Binary, sothat
    you still know if the file is a old, ore New version.
    Only the ASCII Characters are shown of a Binary file.

@{" OverView/Features " Link OverView/Features}
@ENDNODE

@NODE OverView/Features "OverView/Features"
     Here is a List of Some off the things MakeThemYourSelf Can Do:

     * View Contents of Archives.
     * Auto determine What Archive/Text/Powerpacked file etc.
     * View TextFiles online.
     * View TextFiles INSIDE An Archive.
     * View Binary Files, All ASCII Info will be shown.
     * View Binary Files INSIDE an archive.
     * Extract ANY File from an Archive, EVEN DMS Files !!!!.
     * Software is wise enough to see where a Files is on The Device.
     * Send a Extracted file with No Compression ( Quick Send ).

     * Possibility to Extract as MANY files from as MANY archives INSIDE
       the Created new archive, with the compression method you choose !
     * Send a FILE_ID_DIZ File together with the Extracted ore Created
       Archive, This file contains Filedescriptions/sizes etc.
     * A Sysop-Menu where you can send ANY File from ANY Device to you
       Great for Remote MainTainance.
     * A very Nice Graphical User Interface(GUI) for Creation of The Config.

     * Has a powerfull Analyse function to determine what type of file
       it is.
     * A Nice Layout for the Door.
     * No need to Config the Paths of the files, MKTYS Is very capable
       to sort this self out.
     * Usage of WildCards, to find a file on the BBS with a given Pattern
     * Has got many error Checkings to find out why something went wrong
     * Has  Extended LogFile information, which can also be switched of.
     * Is very easy to Install.

     * Send Files from WITHIN the MakeThemYourSelf door, so NO File attach
       to a Message, the files are send Right away (Sysop menuoption.)
     * Auto Extract the number of Bytes a User DownLoaded, so no free
       downLoads, Other than File Attach to a Message where the Bytes are NOT
       Extracted.
     * Automatic Tag System, sothat files donot have to be typed two times.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Options_In_MakeThemYS "Options In MakeThemYS"
   These are All the options you can use in MakeThemYS, read them carefully
   so you understand what can be done with MakeThemYS.

   NOTE: Some Things explained in the Doc, are Only for registered users.


   See @{" Registration " Link Registration}


@{" Option 1, View Files. " Link Option_1,_View_Files.}
@{" Option 2, View a Text File. " Link Option_2,_View_a_Text_File.}
@{" Option 3, Extract a File. " Link Option_3,_Extract_a_File.}
@{" Option 4, List Available Areas. " Link Option_4,_List_Available_Areas.}
@{" Option 5, Select a tagged File " Link Option_5,_Select_a_tagged_File}
@{" Option D, Download a File. " Link Option_D,_Download_a_File.}
@{" Option H, HelpFile " Link Option_H,_HelpFile}
@{" Option Q, Quit MakeThemYS. " Link Option_Q,_Quit_MakeThemYS.}
@{" Option $, Sysop Menu. " Link Option_$,_Sysop_Menu.}
@{" Extra's " Link Extra's}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_1,_View_Files. "Option 1, View Files."

    If you press Option 1, you can view ANY file on the BBS,@{" Wildcards. " Link Wildcards.} are
    allowed.
    If you want to view for example the file : "ARCHIVE.LZH", you can use
    wildcards like this: "ARCH*", ore "ARC#?.LZH" etc.
    If you choose to use wildcards, the searching for that file can take
    some time to find...As you might quess, there might be other files
    on the BBS, which match the wildcard pattern, sothat you can see
    other files that match the wildcard pattern.

    If you know the whole name of the file, the file is found IMMEDIATELY
    so..Searching is not necessary, and the file is listed right away.

    If you choose a file, and it seems that MakeThemYS does not know the file
    format, you will be prompted if you want to Hex/ASCII view this file
    This way you can see the ASCII characters of a Unknown file format..And
    you still be informed of the contents of a file.

    If you select a textFile that is On-line, you can view this textfile On-lin

    Makethemys will show that textfile right away.



    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_2,_View_a_Text_File. "Option 2, View a Text File."

    If you choose Option 2, you can enter a Archive name, again with ore
    without `WildCards....And after the door displays the Contents of that
    archive, you can enter a filename which is IN the archive.
    This Must be A ASCII File, if that is true, the TextFile IN The archive
    will be shown to you online...This way you can read the docs of a Archive
    before you decide to download it.
    If the file you selected is a Binary file, you will be promted if you
    want to see all The ASCII Characters Online....This way you can see if
    a file is a older ore newer version than the one you want, cause
    many programs have dates in them, ore version numbers.


    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_3,_Extract_a_File. "Option 3, Extract a File."

    This option might be THE option you always wanted to use...You will
    be prompted to select a filename, this filename may exist out of
    @{" wildcards. " Link wildcards.}.
    The wildcards allowed are : * and #?, this way, you can first search
    from the Filebase of the BBS, if you do not know the name exactly.
    Offcource, you can also put : *.DMS do search all files with end
    with *.DMS.
    If you don't use Wildcards and enter the filename EXACTLY as it is called,
    the bbs will find it Immediately, and the contents of the file will
    be shown to you.

    After that, you will be prompted to enter a filename you want to extract
    do put in a archive, you can use One file name, but also wildcards are
    allowed in here.
    So, if you enter: *.DOC, all .DOC files will be extracted from the archive.
    After the First file you selected you will be prompted what archivier
    you want to use, this can be :

    Uncompressed, with .LHA, with .LZH ore .ZIP compression...,after the
    choice is made, you can select more files from the selected archive.
    If you DON't want to select file from that archive,
    you can either Download the Created file, ore you can select another
    Archive from the BBS.
    If you choose the last one, you can enter a NEW archive name, and you can
    select files from this one too, Now you won't be prompted to select
    a Archivier used to create the created file, cause you already created
    one.....After you selected more files, these will be extracted and will
    be put in the File you already created.

    Than, you can choose to d/l it, ore...yes, put MORE files in it.
    After you downloaded it, and you choose to make another archive, the
    above described procedure will be replayed again.

    NOTE:
    =====
    If you choose to select/extract file from a DMS file, you HAVE to enter
    the FULL Directory/Filename path....Forget about the device, just put
    the full directory and filename path in it, and the file willl be put
    in your archive.

    See Also: @{" ALLOWDMS " Link ALLOWDMS}


    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_4,_List_Available_Areas. "Option 4, List Available Areas."

    With this Option, you can view all Available areas on this BBS which
    you have Access To.
    This way, you might see an area, you never noticed.
    From these Areas, you can select Any File which you have Access To.



    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_5,_Select_a_tagged_File "Option 5, Select a tagged File"

   This option can be used to select File Numbers, these files were
   AutoMatically tagged by MakeThemYourself, when you used Options

   (1) View Contents
   (2) View Inside an Archive in ASCI or HEX-ASCII (With registered sysops)
   (3) Extract Files from an Archive. 

   So when any of this options were used, and you typed in a file name
   that had a Match, then THAT file is Added to the TagSystem that will
   displays these files in Option 5.

   The purpose of this option is: When you first used for example
   option 1 (View contents of a Archive), and than decided to use
   option 3 (Extract a File), you had to type the filename again,
   or do a scan (in registered versions).

   Now, after you selected a file in option 1,2,3, these files will
   be tagged, and will be displayed in option 5, in there you only
   have to enter the FileNumber, to view the contents, and extract
   a file from it, the search will be done automatically, Now with
   This option you donot have to type a file name 2 times, just
   goto option 5, and select the filenumber.



   @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_D,_Download_a_File. "Option D, Download a File."

    With this Option, you can decide to Download a file, which you created
    before, but decide that you want to add More files into that archive.
    If you decided NOT not add, any more files to that archive you created
    before, you can Press The 'D' Key to download the Marked File.
    The file you Created, will be send to you via MakethemYS.
    This option is Only Active, if you Created an archive but decided not
    to download it yet.
    Sothat that file is Marked....If there were any Marked files, this
    Option is Active, else you will be prompted that you haven't got
    any files Marked.


    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_H,_HelpFile "Option H, HelpFile"

    This option will show the HelpFile, on how to use the door....
    It's the File you are reading now.


    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_Q,_Quit_MakeThemYS. "Option Q, Quit MakeThemYS."

    If you choose This option, you decided to Quit this door, However....
    If you Created a file, and you haven't downloaded it yet, that file
    is still marked for download..And if you want to quit the door, that
    file is still Active for you.
    So, A check is done to see if there are still Marked Files, if there
    are, you will be prompted if you want to [D]ownload the file, or
    if you want to [K]ill, delete the file..If you choose Download,
    The file will be send, and after that, the door will Quit Automatically
    If you Choose to Kill it, the file will be deleted, and you can quit.
    If there ARE Marked files, you MUST have to use these option, so you
    HAVE to DownLoad, ore HAVE to Kill the file.


    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option_$,_Sysop_Menu. "Option $, Sysop Menu."


     This Option CAN BE very dangerous !!!, It gives access to EVERY
     file to ALL DRIVES hooked on your Amiga.

     First, IF you configured the Options: @{" PASSWORD " Link PASSWORD} and @{" ACCESLEVEL " Link ACCESLEVEL}
     you CAN get access to this SysopMenu.
     If you leave these two options OUT of the Config, or you have
     put a ; before it, or you made the acceslevel 32, The $ key
     is TOTALLY Disabled....

     The $ Key will work if:

     * A Users AccesLevel is the same ore HIGHER than the one configured
       in the config.
     * If That is true, the $ Key IS ACTIVE.
     * If the user than press that key, he will be asked for a PassWord
       this password is CASE SenSITive, after he enters the right password
       he has Full Access to the SysopMenu.

@{" Command 1, Send any file. " Link Command_1,_Send_any_file.}
@{" Command 2, View any File. " Link Command_2,_View_any_File.}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Command_1,_Send_any_file. "Command 1, Send any file."

     Now, you can Download ANY file from ANY directory on your drives.
     So if you Choose Option 1, You have to fill in the Full Path AND File-
     definition of the file you want to send.

     Ex. Which file can i send ? :Doors:makethemys/makethemys.CFG

     IF you do not know the name exactly you want it to send, just fill
     in the Directory ore device name ending with a ':' ore '/'.

     Ex1. Which file can i send ? :Doors:MakeThemys/
     Ex2. Which file can i send ? :LIBS:

     So if the input you give ends with a : ore a / than the directory
     contents is first shown to you, after that you know the full name
     and you can fill it in.

     You can see this is a dangerous option cause you can get ANY file
     from the harddisk, but it can be very usefull for sysops that
     maintain there BBS from remote.


     @{" Option $, Sysop Menu. " Link Option_$,_Sysop_Menu.}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Command_2,_View_any_File. "Command 2, View any File."


     NOT AVAILABLE YET...

     @{" Option $, Sysop Menu. " Link Option_$,_Sysop_Menu.}


@ENDNODE

@NODE Extra's "Extra's"

    You always have to enter a minimum of 4 characters of a filename, this
    to shorten the file search if @{" wildcards. " Link wildcards.} are allowed.

    When you want to Extract a file from a DMS file, you HAVE to put the
    full directory path WITH the file name at the prompt.
    Let's Say you want to extract the file : FF0:Libraries/AmigaGuide.library
    You have to fill in: libraries/amigaguide.library.
    @{" WildCards. " Link WildCards.} are NOT allowed in DMS Files.


    @{" Options In MakeThemYS " Link Options_In_MakeThemYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Wildcards. "Wildcards."

    TES*.LZH, Will find : TESTING.LZH,TESCHEME.LZH etc
    TES*    , Will find : TESTING.LHA,TESTING.DMS,TESPE.EXE etc
    *.DMS   , Will find : ALL .DMS FILES.

    HAL#?.ZIP, Will find : HALLOP>.ZIP,HAL%.ZIP etc
    #?E.LHA  , Will find : ARRE.LHA,PLUSEDE.LHA etc

    Amiga Wildcards (#?) can be used also, but it is suggested you only use
    asterix (*), cause these are easier to use.

    If you extract a file from a DMS File, Wildcards are NOT Allowed,If
    you want to use @{" Option 2, View a TextFile " Link Option_2,_View_a_TextFile} inside a Archive, Wildcards
    are Not allowed.

    See Also  @{" WILDCARDS " Link WILDCARDS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Config "Config"


    Provided in the Archive, is a Graphical User Interfase called 'MakeConfig'
    This program is developed to make life for the sysop much easier.

    This Editer, creates and reads a MakeThemYS.DAT file, in this file, all
    options that the MainDoor needs, are stored.

    The Example Config is called MakeThemYS.DAT, if this file is in the
    Door:MakeThemYS/ directory, than those options are loaded automatically
    in the Configediter.
    If it's NOT present, it will Use the Default values, edit those to the
    values you want.

@{" Options in MakeConfig " Link Options_in_MakeConfig}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Options_in_MakeConfig "Options in MakeConfig"
    * PATH Archiviers

    Ex. C:

    Here you have to Fill in a Path, where ALL your archivier programs
    Are Stored.
    In this Case ALL Programs will Be in The C: Directory, Also, You have
    to put the program 'WhatIS', in this directory.

    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------

    * PATH New Archive

    Ex. T:

    Here you have to fill in the path, where the File made by MakeThemYS
    will be stored.
    This file is Called: X_MakeThem.XXX, Where the first X, is the first
    Number that is send, and the second 3 X's are the extension.

    Like: 1_MakeThem.LZH, then, if a user downloads a other file, the next
    Name will be 2_MakeThem.XXX, Ore....Nothing if he chooses to Use
    Uncompressed.


    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------


   * PATH Extracted Files

    Ex. DH0:T/

    Here you have to put a Path, where the extracted file(s) will be stored.
    Offcourse they will be automatically deleted.

    So the files which a user will choose to download.



    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------

   * PATH BBSLogo

    Ex. S:BBSLogo.TXT

    This File will be added by MakethemYs to the Created File.
    So you can put your own BBSLogo, Ore DisPlayMe's in the Archive that
    makeThemYS Creates.


    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------


   * Allow FULL DMS View

    Ex. Enabled

    If This Button is Enabled, MakeThemYS, will do a FULL Listing
    of a .DMS File.

    If it is Disabled, i will do a Normal DMS Viewing (C:DMS VIEW TEST.DMS)

    MTYS, Will first check to see if the FF0: device exists, than it
    will do a Quick Format on that Disk.
    Don't worry, Only FF0: will Be Formatted for safety reasons.
    After That, DMS Will be invoked to UnDMS The selected DMS File.
    Than, if it's done, it will do a List, and will show that list to the
    user, this list contains the FULL Contents of the DMS File.


    NOTE: This Option is ONLY Active to Registered Users.

    See @{" Registration " Link Registration}


    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------


    * Logfile Active

    Ex. Enabled

    If this Checkbox is Enabled, A Log File is Created in the
    Doors:MakeThemYS/  Dir......
    if you don't want any Log Information, Just Disable the CheckBox.


    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------


    * Allow Wildcards

    Ex. Enabled

    If This CheckBox is Enabled, WildCards Are allowed by users.
    If it's Disabled, No wildcards are allowed In MakeThemYS.

    NOTE: This Option is ONLY Active in a Registered version, so Wildcards
          can not be used.

    See @{" Registration " Link Registration}


    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Allow Hex-View

    Ex. Enabled

    If this Checkbox is Enabled, Viewing of UNKNOWN Files is Possible
    with a Util called WhatIS.
    This util wil get ALL ASCII Characters from the Unknown file and display
    it to user,the util is started by the door.

    After MTYS Returns that it found the unknown FileFormat, it will ask
    the user if he/she wants to Hex/ASCII View the file...If he does,
    Whatis will be called to make that Listing.

    If This Checkbox is Disabled, there will be NO prompt to ask if the user
    wants the hex/Ascii view the file.

    The Hex/ascii View option is ONLY available in @{" Option 1, View Files. " Link Option_1,_View_Files.}
    And in @{" Option 2, View a Text File. " Link Option_2,_View_a_Text_File.}


    NOTE: This Option is ONLY Active in a Registered versions.

    See @{" Registration " Link Registration}

    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------

    * SysopMenu Enabled/Disabled (From the menu, on top of the Screen)


    If This MenuBar is Enabled,Than the @{" ACCESLEVEL " Link ACCESLEVEL} slider and the
    @{" PASSWORD " Link PASSWORD} StringGadget is Enabled.

    So, if you want the SysopMenu to be Active,Just Enable MenuBar,ore
    else use the Disable function if you don't want the SysopMenu to be Active


    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Password Sysop-Menu

    Ex. sECrEt

    This PassWord is used, to enter the Sysop Menu, you have to enter
    the correct password to enter the menu.

    This Password is Case Sensitive.


    ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    ----------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Acceslevel

    Ex. 31

    This Acceslevel is used to determine What acceslevel a user has to have
    to enter the sysop menu with the '$' Key from the MainMenu.

    MTYS Will first check if the SysopMenu is Enabled in the Config,
    if not,than the SysopMenu can't EVER be accessed to, not
    even by the sysop.

    In this example, A User HAS to have a Minimum acceslevel of 31 to enter
    the sysopMenu, and after that, a @{" PASSWORD " Link PASSWORD} is asked also for higher
    security.
    If both things are right, you can acces the Sysop Menu with the '$' Key.

    So: If the config states:

    ACCESLEVEL 5
    @{" PASSWORD " Link PASSWORD} TEST

    Then ALL Users who have a minimum of acceslevel 5, and those who know
    the right password, have access to the Sysop Menu.
    In this case, The '$' Key will work for them.

    =========================================================================

    * File ID Adding

    If you have this CheckBox enabled, the user will be prompted before he
    DownLoads a file, if he wants to receive the FILE_ID file.
    The file is called: FILEx_ID_DIZ where X is also the number of the
    Created archive.

    This file contains all information on the file he extracted.
    Here's a Example of the file that will be included in the archive
    that MakeThemYS will make for a User:

    -------------------------------------------------------------------------
    [- Created by MakeThemYs V0.08e[Registered], Registered by Marco Valk -]

    Original Name : AREBOOT.LHA
    Description   : Auto reboot na software failure
    Extracted File: AUTOREADME [5305] Bytes
    Extracted File: .INFO [5305] Bytes
    -------------------------------------------------------------------------

    In This example you can see What files a User extracted from which Archive.
    This is a Very Nice Feature i think, cause this way the user has a reminder
    from which archives he extracted some files.

    If the CheckBox is disabled in the Config, the prompt to add this file
    to the users Archive won't be shown.

    So: If enabled, the user will be asked if he wants to add the file_id
        info into the archive.

    NOTE: if a User selects a Uncompressed file, a prompt AFTER the download
          will be displayed, if he wants to receive this file_id, if he
          selects YES, the file is SEND in stead of ADDED to a archive.



@{" Example MakeThemYS.DAT " Link Example_MakeThemYS.DAT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Example_MakeThemYS.DAT "Example MakeThemYS.DAT"
     Put This example in the Doors:MakethemYs/MakeThemYS.DAT
     See The @{" Options in MakeConfig " Link Options_in_MakeConfig} for Full Explanation off the KeyWords.



@ENDNODE

@NODE Installing_MTYS "Installing MTYS"
    Read this Part carefully sothat there can be NO Mistakes with installing
    the door MakeThemYS.

    [1] Create a Directory Called MakeThemYS in you Doors: directory

    [2] Copy the following files in this directory:

        * MakeThemYS
        * MakeConfig
        * MakeThemYS.DAT

        * Archive.GR1
        * Archive.TXT
        * Help.TXT
        * MakeItMenu.GR1
        * MakeItMenu.TXT
        * SysopMenu.TXT
        * SysopMenu.GR1

        * All the Documentation files. (Suggestion :In a MakeThemYS/Docs/
          directory)

        * For Registered users: The MakeThemYS.key

          See @{" Registration " Link Registration} for more details

    [3] Start the program MakeConfig, to Edit all The options that
        are available for MakeThemYS.

        See: @{" Options in MakeConfig " Link Options_in_MakeConfig} for more Info.

    [4] Copy ALL Archiviers AND the util WhatIS to the path
        you defined after Path Archiviers, be sure there is the Format command
        in your SYS:System/ directory.

    [5] Make an entry in your Files.Menu file like this:

        ---------------------Cut--------------------------
        Option 'V':
        Function MultiRundoor Doors:MakeThemYS/MakeThemYS
        end
        ---------------------Cut--------------------------


    [7] Copy the fms.device to you DEVS: directory

    [8] Create a directory on your harddisk, called FMS.A Nice Place is in
        the DOORS:MakeThemYS/ Directory.

    - make a assignment: ASSIGN FMS: PATH:WHERE/YOUR/FMSDIR/IS
    - Make an entry in your mountlist for the FF0: device, see the supplied
      mountlist.
    - Mount FF0: , read the fms.doc file how....

    This device is used to Unarc the .DMS files to your FF0: assigned device
    and is VERY important for proper installing the Device...

    [9] Be sure there is the Format command in your sys:system/ directory,this
        command is used to clean up your FF0: device....Don't worry it WON'T
        format your hardDisk...Only your FF0: device.

    [10] Now you are ready to Go.

    [11] See @{" External Programs " Link External_Programs}


@{" External Programs " Link External_Programs}
@ENDNODE

@NODE External_Programs "External Programs"
    These following programs are needed to make MTYS work
    you see several versions etc that are needed to make
    work MTYS 100%.
    These programs are tested with MTYS, but other version might
    work also.
    Just experiment with it if you can not get these versions.
    But Than i can not guarantee that it will work.
    I can Not quarantee anything, but this setup works 100% on
    my System.

    * ZOO Version v2.01 by J.Brian Waters Size: 41560 Bytes
    * LHA Version v1.50r by S.Boberg, Other versions Might work also.
    * Unarj v1.15 By R.K Jung/H.Schneider, other versions might work.
    * Pkax v1.0
    * UNDms 2.04 (Device-Masher-System), Newer versions Might work.
    * DMS v1.53, Newer versions Might work.
    * Zip v2.0.1 (Sep 18,'93)
    * Unzip v5.1d3 BETA (18 Feb '93)
    * Shrink v1.01b By M.Meixner (For .SHR files Only)
    * WhatIs v2.5 by J.Tyberghein (07 Apr '92)
    * List v37.5 (other versions might work)
    * Copy v38.1 (other versions might work)
    * Delete v37.8 (other versions might work,This is needed to delete
      Files which are extracted with wildcards.
    * Decrunch (Util to decrunch PowerPacked files)

    * All These programs except registered versions can be get from nearly
      every PD BBS.....If you Can't get them, ore you got some versions
      that don't work, get them from me.

      See @{" registration " Link registration} for more details.


    @{" Installing MTYS " Link Installing_MTYS}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Registration "Registration"
     MakeThemYS is a 'ShareWare' Concept, i did this because nobody seems to
     do anything for a program.
     I released several other doors like 'RunCLI','AutoUpdate','Sysinfo' etc
